I've reviewed your project — it's a well-structured, impressive idea that combines ML forecasting + agentic AI + a real-world problem domain. Here's my honest take:

What's great about it:

Real-world relevance (solar/grid management is a hot domain)
Clear two-milestone structure (forecasting → AI agent)
Good dataset choice (8760 rows, hourly, feature-rich)
The RAG + LangGraph extension makes it portfolio-worthy
Totally buildable. Let's go step by step.

Here's the high-level roadmap so you know where we're headed, then we'll dive into Step 1:

✅ Project Setup — folder structure, virtual env, git init
📊 Data Loading & EDA — understand the dataset
🔧 Feature Engineering — time features, lag features
🤖 Baseline Model — Linear Regression
🚀 Advanced Models — Random Forest, XGBoost
🧠 Agentic AI Assistant — LangChain/LangGraph + RAG
🖥️ Streamlit UI — interactive web interface
☁️ Deployment — Hugging Face Spaces or Streamlit Cloud
