✅ Step 1 Complete — Here's what was built and WHY:
Folder Structure explained:
Folder	Purpose
data/raw/	Your original CSV goes here — never modified
data/processed/	Cleaned, feature-engineered data saved here
notebooks/	EDA and experimentation (messy is OK here)
src/forecasting/	Clean, reusable Python modules for ML
src/agent/	LangGraph agent code lives here
src/ui/	Streamlit app code
models/	Saved .pkl model files
reports/	AI-generated grid reports
Why this structure? It separates concerns cleanly — notebooks for exploration, src/ for production-quality code. This is how real ML projects are organized.

📌 Git Commit Message:
feat: initialize project structure

- Set up folder layout (data, src, notebooks, models, reports)
- Add requirements.txt with Phase 1 ML dependencies
- Add .gitignore for Python/ML project
- Add README with project overview and setup instructions
🔜 Your action items before Step 2:
Download your dataset — grab the Solar Power Generation dataset from Kaggle
Place the CSV in data/raw/
Run on your machine:
bash
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate   # or venv\Scripts\activate on Windows
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   git init && git add . && git commit -m "feat: initialize project structure"
Once your dataset is in place, Step 2 is Data Loading & EDA — we'll explore the dataset, visualize patterns, and understand what we're working with. Ready?

